{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Hierarchies","anchor":"Hierarchies","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The Strong “call for action” on the page should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), hierarchy: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\", hierarchy: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Styles","anchor":"Styles","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for following states disabled, pressed, hovered or normal (i.e. enabled)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Colored Surface","anchor":"Colored-Surface","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrom."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative button on a colored surface."}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/48a788-button","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only, icon only or text with icon."}],"metadata":{"title":"OUDSButton","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents10OUDSButtonV","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon: